com.percussion.search
Interface IPSSearchResultsProcessor

All Superinterfaces:
IPSExtension
All Known Implementing Classes:
PSCleanFolderSearchResultsExit
public interface IPSSearchResultsProcessor
extends IPSExtension

This interface is implemented by extensions capable of processing the search result rows.

The search handler will construct an instance of this class and run it to post process the search results that were generated by the search handler. The implementing class can modify column values for each search result row. It can add additional row(s) by cloning row(s). However,

  • it cannot add or delete columns to a row
  • it cannot add a new row without cloning an existing one.

The implementation of this extension must be thread safe.

Method Detail

processRows

List processRows(Object[] params,
                 List rows,
                 IPSRequestContext request)
                 throws PSExtensionProcessingException
The actual implementation of the row processing as described in the class description.

Parameters:
params - parameters to the extension as documented in the definition of the extension. Never null, may be empty.
rows - a list of the search result rows, These are the rows the implementer may want to modify. Never null or empty.
request - request context object, never null.
Returns:
A list of modified rows. Must not be null may be empty.
Throws:
PSExtensionProcessingException - implementation can throw this exception if any error occurs during processing.
